      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant. This specimen retains its factory-spec vacuum routing and original Hitachi HT12 units, delivering a seamless boost transition at 4,500 RPM. The chassis remains structurally pristine, preserving the 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry that defined its class. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent compression tests yield optimal, uniform results across all rotor faces. This is a turnkey example of peak JDM engineering, showing zero signs of thermal degradation or synchro wear.",
